b'Disability and Human Development'
b'Admissions and Programs'
b'Assistive Technology Certificate'
b'Earn your Assistive Technology Certificate from a CAAHEP- accredited program'
b'UIC-DHD Assistive Technology Certificate Program (ATCP) is a CAAHEP-accredited Assistive Technology Program designed to give you hands-on, practical training in assessing and implementing assistive technologies. The ATCP\xe2\x80\x99s goal is to train working professionals to deliver state of the art assistive technology services and solutions\xc2\xa0for people with physical, cognitive, or sensory disabilities. You\xe2\x80\x99ll learn how to properly analyze needs, select appropriate technology, and train people in the use of these devices.'
b'Each AT course at UIC is taught by a instructor with extensive clinical experience in their course topic areas.\xc2\xa0 The core faculty are faculty members in the Department of Disability and Human Development, are senior clinicians in the UIC\xc2\xa0Assistive Technology Unit\xc2\xa0and are RESNA Certified Assistive Technology Professionals (ATPs).\xc2\xa0Adjunct faculty are recognized AT professionals working in a variety of settings.'
b'Assistive Technology Unit'
b'Our program is a flexible packaging of 12 credit hours that can be taken entirely online or through a combination of online and lab-based courses at UIC.'
